========================================================================================
PING SCALING TEST — the check that is an experiment, not a statistic
========================================================================================
PING requires the peak frequency to fall roughly as 1/tau_GABA, because
inhibitory decay sets the cycle period. A drive harmonic, a statistical
fluctuation, and a resonance set by any other time constant will not move.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
LIF baseline
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   tau_GABA   rate_E   rate_I   gamma p    prom   null    PEAK   per-seed peaks
        2ms      8.9     59.1     0.588    6.87   6.73    37.7   [37.7, 55.3, 35.3]
        5ms      6.0     32.5     0.011    8.70   6.69    49.1   [49.1, 41.0, 50.2]
       10ms      4.8     21.0     0.027    7.97   6.53    35.2   [33.1, 45.4, 35.2]
       20ms      4.3     14.5     0.418    6.85   6.45    38.7   [38.7, 54.6, 33.3]

  tau_GABA changed by 10x  (2 -> 20 ms)
  peak frequency changed by 0.97x  (37.7 -> 38.7 Hz, i.e. 1.0 Hz)
  => PEAK DOES NOT SCALE. NOT PING. Whatever this peak is, it is not
     the excitatory-inhibitory loop oscillating. No claim of emergent
     gamma is warranted, regardless of how many screens it passed.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
